Running a CloudReady ChromeOS VM in Virtualbox
ðŸ’¡ NOTE: This method uses an older version of CloudReady Free. The latest release is incompatible with VirtualBox due to graphics requirements

Open a web browser and download the CloudReady .ova Download
Launch VirtualBox
Select File > Import Appliance...
Click the Browse icon > Navigate to the downloaded .ova file > Select CloudReady_Free_x64_Virtualbox.ova
Click Next and then Import
Make sure the CloudReady_Free_x64 VM is selected and click Start > Normal
Select a Language and Keyboard Layout > Click Continue
Click Accept and install
Click Continue without Flash
Enter your Google/GMail account and password
Select an icon for your user account > Click OK
Click the Take a tour button
Welcome to CloudReady, ChromeOS
